==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: -lin
<hw>-lin</hw> }</mhw>. <ety>[From NL. <ets>Areca</ets>, a genus of palms
bearing betel nut.]</ety> <def>An oily liquid substance,
<chform>C8H13O2N</chform>, the chief alkaloid of the betel nut, to which
the latter owes its anthelmintic action.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> arecholine; arecaline; methylarecaidin; methyl
N-methyltetrahydronicotinate;
<chname>1,2,5,6-tetrahydro-1-methyl-3-pyridinecarboxylic acid methyl
ester</chname>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

